name: The Hanged Man
description: "The Hanged Man" is a short story inspired on the tarot card and on this thinking of what’s real and what’s not real. It’s about this man who sees himself stuck in a loop, wandering around trying to find out what’s real, what’s causing him this pain. But reality is a funny topic, because how can we know what is real and what's not? Do you think that he’s crazy? Does his wife really exist? Does he live next to this strange house? We will never know. But what I want to know is: what do you think? Do you see yourself stuck in a loop too? Do you also question reality?
